<TITLE> Defaulters with injunction having unfair edge: CEC </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 5 (bdnews24.com)  The chief election commissioner said on Friday said bank loan and utility bill defaulters were frustrating the EC's efforts to ensure that all candidates started the race on a level playing field. ATM Shamsul Huda Huda said some candidates, who would have otherwise been barred for defaulting on loan and utility bill payments under new electoral laws, have secured court injunctions to get become eligible. "Many influential loan and bill defaulters are taking part in the election through court injunctions. But other defaulters have not been able to do that. So discrimination among the candidates are there." He said they had little to do when the court issued stay orders. He made the remarks at a discussion styled "Ninth parliamentary elections: our mass media" in Dhaka University's Nabab Ali Chowdhury Senate Bhaban. bd
